review.description:
After a day of shopping we went in search of a local ice cream shop, and found VanLeeuwen's on Bergen Street, near Smith Street in Brooklyn. Just yum. Simply, just yum. We sampled various flavors with the following results:

- chocolate was smooth and rich, without any hint of chalkiness;
- earl grey tasted like the creamy frozen equivalent of a cup of its namesake tea;
- candied ginger was creamy and sweet with candied bits of real ginger and just the right amount of a peppery bite;
- sea salt caramel had a nice burnt sugar taste;
- pistachio was flavorful, but without any nuts, which was slightly disappointing. 

They also have a vegan ice cream selection and a small selection of pastries and coffee. 

All in all a great find, and I'm looking forward to returning to Brooklyn with an empty cooler, and returning to PA with it filled with candied ginger ice cream (my surprise favorite, since I have hitherto been a pistachio gal.)
